name: Ocean Shores Convention Center
address: 120 West Chance a La Mer Northwest, Ocean Shores WA, 98569
vaccines: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine
info: This clinic is held within the Ocean Shores Convention Center. This clinic is for the 2nd dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine and the one-dose Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) COVID-19 vaccine. Both the Moderna vaccine and the Janssen vaccine is only available to adults 18 years and older. The supply of the Janssen vaccine is limited. For the 2nd Moderna dose, you must have had the MODERNA VACCINE for your first vaccine in order to get the second dose of the Moderna vaccine. You CANNOT mix brands of the COVID-19 vaccine. Please bring a face covering to your appointment that covers the mouth and the nose and, if you are getting your second dose, please bring your vaccination card. If you cannot locate your vaccine card, proof of first vaccination and type of vaccine must be provided. All persons receiving the vaccine are required to stay under observation 15-30 minutes post-vaccination.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Toledo First Baptist Church
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in. ++MODERNA vaccine will also be available. ++ However, any 1st Dose Moderna clients will need to seek their 2nd dose in 28 days with an alternate provider.                                                                                          
Please note: Johnson & Johnson and Moderna vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements.

This clinic is located at and hosted by Toledo First Baptist Church in partnership with Lewis County DPHSS, WA DOH and WA National Guard. This is a walk in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind.  **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation.

Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided.

If this is your 2nd dose Moderna vaccination please bring your vaccination card from your 1st Moderna dose. If you do not have your card you may register with and confirm proof of vaccination at https://wa.myir.net/                      
 Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing. - It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. Given Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site.  **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

info: ***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available. Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.

name: Evergreen State Fairgrounds Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
**************THIS IS MODERNA CLINIC******************
Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
